body:
The validator should return an `{ error }` instead of throwing it:

```
function (data) {
      try {
        const result = schema.validateSync(data, yupOptions)
        return { value: result }
      } catch (e) {
        return { error: e }
      }
    }
```

PS: there is this `joi-compiler` already cooked too: https://github.com/Eomm/joi-compiler
PPS2: it works with the sync hook because the `done()` does not propagate the error I think, but it worth checking it deeper
